{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C2180 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2180 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"pos":[598,618],"content":"Compiler Error C2180","linkify":"Compiler Error C2180","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C2180","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"controlling expression has type 'type'","pos":[619,657]},{"content":"The controlling expression in an <ph id=\"ph1\">`if`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph2\">`while`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph3\">`for`</ph>, or <ph id=\"ph4\">`do`</ph> statement is an expression cast to <ph id=\"ph5\">`void`</ph>.","pos":[664,769],"source":"The controlling expression in an `if`, `while`, `for`, or `do` statement is an expression cast to `void`."},{"content":"To fix this issue, change the controlling expression to one that produces a <ph id=\"ph1\">`bool`</ph> or a type that can be converted to <ph id=\"ph2\">`bool`</ph>.","pos":[770,895],"source":" To fix this issue, change the controlling expression to one that produces a `bool` or a type that can be converted to `bool`."},{"content":"The following sample generates C2180:","pos":[902,939]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C2180 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-cpp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"error-reference\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C2180\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C2180\"\nms.assetid: ea71b39e-b977-48a7-b7bd-af68ef5e263b\ncaps.latest.revision: 11\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C2180\ncontrolling expression has type 'type'  \n  \n The controlling expression in an `if`, `while`, `for`, or `do` statement is an expression cast to `void`. To fix this issue, change the controlling expression to one that produces a `bool` or a type that can be converted to `bool`.  \n  \n The following sample generates C2180:  \n  \n```  \n// C2180.c  \n  \nint main() {  \n   while ((void)1)   // C2180  \n      return 1;  \n   while (1)         // OK  \n      return 0;  \n}  \n```"}